How to set up the project (STEP-BY-STEP)
1. Install required tools

You need:

GitHub Desktop
https://desktop.github.com/
Git LFS
https://git-lfs.com/
Unreal Engine 5.7

2. Log into GitHub Desktop
Open GitHub Desktop
Sign in with GitHub account
Make sure it’s the same account

3. Clone the repository
Open GitHub Desktop
Click File → Clone repository
Go to GitHub.com tab
Select your repo (Untitled_Game)
Choose location (example):
Documents/GitHub/
Click Clone

4. Enable Git LFS (VERY IMPORTANT)

After cloning, you MUST do this once:

Open terminal (or Git Bash) in the project folder:
git lfs install

That’s it —tracking is already set from your .gitattributes.

🎮 5. Open the project

Inside the folder:

Double-click:

Untitled_Game.uproject

Unreal will:

generate missing files locally
set up the project

6. Create their own branch (CRITICAL)

In GitHub Desktop:

Click Current branch
Click New branch
Name it:
feature/your-name-task

Examples:

feature/ethan-audio
feature/robin-ai
feature/ludvig-level1

Then switch to that branch

7. Daily workflow (what they should always do)

Every time they work:

Open GitHub Desktop
Click Fetch origin
Click Pull origin (if needed)
Make sure they are on their branch
Open Unreal
Work

8. Saving work

After working:
-Open GitHub Desktop
-Review changes
-Write a clear message: example/Added enemy movement
-Click Commit to branch
-Click Push origin
